<li id="cite_note-23"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1133582631"><cite id="CITEREFNienhuys2008" class="citation web cs1">Nienhuys, Han-Kwang (2008). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.lagom.nl/lcd-test/gamma_calibration.php">"Gamma calibration"</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2018-11-30</span></span>. <q>The reason for using 48% rather than 50% as a luminance is that many LCD screens have saturation issues in the last 5 percent of their brightness range that would distort the gamma measurement.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Gamma+calibration&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.aulast=Nienhuys&amp;rft.aufirst=Han-Kwang&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lagom.nl%2Flcd-test%2Fgamma_calibration.php&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGamma+correction" class="Z3988"></span></span>
