<li id="cite_note-31"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1133582631"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://github.com/mozilla/mozjpeg/issues/193">"Gamma-correct chroma subsampling · Issue #193 · mozilla/mozjpeg"</a>. <i>GitHub</i>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=GitHub&amp;rft.atitle=Gamma-correct+chroma+subsampling+%C2%B7+Issue+%23193+%C2%B7+mozilla%2Fmozjpeg&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fmozilla%2Fmozjpeg%2Fissues%2F193&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGamma+correction" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Archived at <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://ghostarchive.org/varchive/youtube/20211211/LKnqECcg6Gw">Ghostarchive</a> and the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20150321235204/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LKnqECcg6Gw">Wayback Machine</a>: <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1133582631"><cite id="CITEREFMinute_Physics2015" class="citation web cs1">Minute Physics (March 20, 2015). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LKnqECcg6Gw">"Computer Color is Broken"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/YouTube" title="YouTube">YouTube</a></i>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=YouTube&amp;rft.atitle=Computer+Color+is+Broken&amp;rft.date=2015-03-20&amp;rft.au=Minute+Physics&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DLKnqECcg6Gw&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGamma+correction" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-33"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-33">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1133582631"><cite id="CITEREFNovak2016" class="citation web cs1">Novak, John (September 21, 2016). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://blog.johnnovak.net/2016/09/21/what-every-coder-should-know-about-gamma/">"What every coder should know about gamma"</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=What+every+coder+should+know+about+gamma&amp;rft.date=2016-09-21&amp;rft.aulast=Novak&amp;rft.aufirst=John&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fblog.johnnovak.net%2F2016%2F09%2F21%2Fwhat-every-coder-should-know-about-gamma%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGamma+correction" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-34"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-34">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1133582631"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://github.com/GNOME/gegl/blob/mainline/gegl/buffer/gegl-sampler-lohalo.c">"GNOME/gegl: gegl-sampler-lohalo.c"</a>. <i>GitHub</i>. <q>Sigmoidization was invented by N. Robidoux as a method of minimizing the over and undershoots that arise out of filtering with kernel with one more negative lobe. It basically consists of resampling through a colorspace in which gamut extremes are "far" from midtones.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=GitHub&amp;rft.atitle=GNOME%2Fgegl%3A+gegl-sampler-lohalo.c&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2FGNOME%2Fgegl%2Fblob%2Fmainline%2Fgegl%2Fbuffer%2Fgegl-sampler-lohalo.c&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGamma+correction" class="Z3988"></span></span>
